<!DOCTYPE HTML>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>SyncSounds: Atmosphere</title>
    <style>
        .topbar {
            overflow: hidden;
            background-color: #fff;
        }

        .topbar button {
            float: left;
            display: block;
            color: black;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 14px 16px;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .topbar button:hover {
            background-color: #ddd;
            color: black;
        }
    </style>
</head>
    <body>
	    <div class="topbar">
		  <button onclick="location.href='/';">Home</button>
		  <button onclick="location.href='/login';">Login</button>
		  <button onclick="location.href='/insert';">Add Song</button>
		  <button onclick="location.href='/musicality';">Musicality</button>  
		  <button onclick="location.href='/energy';">Energy</button>  
		  <button onclick="location.href='/atmosphere';">Atmosphere</button>
		  <button onclick="location.href='/volume';">Volume</button>
		  <button onclick="location.href='/leaderboard';">Album Leaderboard</button>
		  <button onclick="location.href='/random';">Random Song & Video</button>
		</div>
		
        <h2>Atmosphere</h2>
        
        <b>Valence:</b> a measure from 0.0 to 1.0 describing the musical positiveness conveyed by a track. Tracks with high valence sound more positive (e.g. happy, cheerful, euphoric), while tracks with low valence sound more negative (e.g. sad, depressed, angry).

        <h3>Top 10 Songs for Valence:</h3>
        <table border = 1, cellpadding = 3px, cellspacing = 0px>
            <tr>
            	<th>Rank</th>
                <th>Song</th>
                <th>Artist</th>
                <th>Valence</th>
            </tr>
            {{#Valences}}
                <tr>
                	<td>{{rank}}</td>
                    <td>{{Track}}</td>
                    <td>{{Artist}}</td>
                    <td>{{Stat}}</td>
                </tr>
            {{/Valences}}
        </table>
        
        <h3>Average Valence: {{ValenceAvg}}</h3>
        
        <b>Liveness:</b> detects the presence of an audience in the recording. Higher liveness values represent an increased probability that the track was performed live. A value above 0.8 provides strong likelihood that the track is live.<br>
        
        <h3>Top 10 Songs for Liveness:</h3>
        <table border = 1, cellpadding = 3px, cellspacing = 0px>
            <tr>
            	<th>Rank</th>
                <th>Song</th>
                <th>Artist</th>
                <th>Liveness</th>
            </tr>
            {{#Livenesses}}
                <tr>
                	<td>{{rank}}</td>
                    <td>{{Track}}</td>
                    <td>{{Artist}}</td>
                    <td>{{Stat}}</td>
                </tr>
            {{/Livenesses}}
        </table>
        
        <h3>Average Liveness: {{LivenessAvg}}</h3>
    </body>
</html>
